</taxonomicName>
species based on male wing characters
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="50" type="key">
<key pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" box="[151,1436,796,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,796,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">(1) Dorsal wing surfaces with violet sheen.................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" box="[151,1436,825,847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,825,847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
- Dorsal wing surfaces without violet, but goldish sheen (
<collectingCountry box="[761,810,826,847]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Peru</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[818,892,825,847]" country="Peru" name="Ancash" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Ancash</collectingRegion>
)...................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Johnson, 1990" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1990" box="[1175,1436,825,847]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Penaincisalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurulenta">
<emphasis box="[1175,1291,825,847]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">P. aurulenta</emphasis>
Johnson, 1990
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" box="[151,1436,855,877]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,855,877]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">(2) Ventral forewing area below discalis orange.............................................................. (3)</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" box="[151,1436,884,906]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,884,906]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">- Ventral forewing below discalis brown or grey............................................................. (4)</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" box="[151,1436,913,936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,913,936]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
(3) Dorsal forewing androconia black, hindwing black border fading towards tornus (
<collectingCountry box="[1011,1060,914,935]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Peru</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[1067,1141,913,935]" country="Peru" name="Ancash" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Ancash</collectingRegion>
)..... 
<taxonomicName authority="Balint, 2001" authorityName="Balint" authorityYear="2001" box="[1230,1436,913,935]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Penaincisalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezi">
<emphasis box="[1230,1312,914,935]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">P. perezi</emphasis>
Bálint, 2001
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
- Dorsal forewing androconia grey, hindwing black border visible as far as the tornus (
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1089,943,964]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Peru</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[1097,1195,943,965]" country="Peru" name="Apurimac" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Apurímac</collectingRegion>
).................................................................................... 
<emphasis box="[1019,1070,973,994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">P. sp.</emphasis>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Balint Zs. &amp; Katona, G. &amp; Kertesz, K." box="[1120,1291,972,994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" pagination="137 - 144" refId="ref4391" refString="Balint Zs., Katona, G. &amp; Kertesz, K. (2019) A new species of Penaincisalia (Lepidoptera: Lycaenidae) from Peru. Opuscula Zoologica, 50 (2), 137 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.18348 / opzool. 2019.2.137" type="journal article" year="2019">
Bálint 
<emphasis box="[1185,1227,972,994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
: figures 25-28)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
(4) Larger (forewing costa length 
<quantity box="[513,582,1002,1023]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
), dorsal wing surface dark rufous brown, ventral forewing surface median and postmedian region with same colour (
<collectingCountry box="[471,520,1031,1052]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Peru</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[528,626,1031,1053]" country="Peru" name="Apurimac" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Apurímac</collectingRegion>
)................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Balint, 2019" authorityName="Balint" authorityYear="2019" box="[1239,1436,1031,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Penaincisalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alina">
<emphasis box="[1239,1311,1031,1052]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">P. alina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Balint Zs. &amp; Katona, G. &amp; Kertesz, K." box="[1318,1436,1031,1053]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" pagination="137 - 144" refId="ref4391" refString="Balint Zs., Katona, G. &amp; Kertesz, K. (2019) A new species of Penaincisalia (Lepidoptera: Lycaenidae) from Peru. Opuscula Zoologica, 50 (2), 137 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.18348 / opzool. 2019.2.137" type="journal article" year="2019">Bálint, 2019</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,796,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
- Smaller (forewing costa 
<quantity box="[461,531,1060,1082]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
), dorsal wing surface vivid orange, ventral forewing surface grey in median and brownish grey in postmedian areas (
<collectingCountry box="[429,478,1090,1111]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Peru</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[487,619,1089,1111]" country="Peru" name="Huancavelica" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Huancavelica</collectingRegion>
)................................................... 
